sourceQuestion:
Consider the following C functions:

int tob(int b, int* arr) {
    int i;
    for (i = 0; b > 0; i++) {
        if (b % 2) arr[i] = 1;
        else arr[i] = 0;
        b = b / 2;
    }
    return (i);
}

int pp(int a, int b) {
    int arr[20];
    int i, tot = 1, ex, len;
    ex = a;
    len = tob(b, arr);
    for (i = 0; i < len; i++) {
        if (arr[i] == 1)
            tot = tot * ex;
        ex = ex * ex;
    }
    return tot;
}

The value returned by pp(3, 4) is __________

A. 81
B. 27
C. 64
D. 9

